Description:
    Scaffolds with the same parameters as the orginal "scaffold" generator but
    produces localized views and controller flashes.

    Automatically adds pagination if gem "mislav-will_paginate" is available,
    so be sure to add a require for "will_paginate" or you'll get an exeption.

    The generator will copy and generate all needed localization files, but
    you need to add the following lines to the initialization of Rails in
    "environment.rb" or you'll see only missing localization strings.

    Rails::Initializer.run do |config|
      config.i18n.load_path += Dir[Rails.root.join('lib', 'locale', '*.{rb,yml}')]
      config.i18n.load_path += Dir[Rails.root.join('app', 'locale', '*.{rb,yml}')]
      config.i18n.default_locale = :de
    end

Examples:
    `./script/generate localized_scaffold post`
    `./script/generate localized_scaffold post title:string body:text published:boolean`
    `./script/generate localized_scaffold purchase order_id:integer amount:decimal`
